",4
verbderiv,Verbal roots and stems,"<a id='verbderiv'></a>

## Classes of verbs

[Language yab](LanguageTable?#cldf:yab) verb roots can be divided into those yielding an intransitive stem, and those yielding a transitive stem.
The only inflectional criterion distinguishing the two classes is the third person prefix [Morpheme t3](MorphsetTable?no_translation#cldf:t3), which can only occur on transitive stems.
Thus, transitive [Morpheme yawanka-kill](MorphsetTable?#cldf:yawanka-kill) can take [Morpheme t3](MorphsetTable?no_translation#cldf:t3) <a class=""exref"" example_id=""convfemgrme-217""release=""False"" ></a>, but intransitive [Morpheme yaruwa-laugh](MorphsetTable?#cldf:yaruwa-laugh) does not <a class=""exref"" example_id=""convrisamaj-42""release=""False"" ></a>.

[Example convfemgrme-217,convrisamaj-42](ExampleTable?ids=convfemgrme-217,convrisamaj-42&example_counter=13#cldf:__all__)

<span title='subclass of intransitive (?'>❓</span>: -nëpëkë and -tëpëkë)

* detransitive
* ditransitive
* ""n-adding""
* accidental lability
* ijtëri

* Note that all transitive verbs are consonant‑initial, whether etymologically or not because [Morpheme ylk](MorphsetTable?#cldf:ylk) is added to all vowel‑initial roots
* the _y‑_ disappears when preceded by the detransitivizer <span title='examples for detransitivized verbs'>❗️</span> <span title='what about V-initial intransitive verbs? how are they inflected?'>❓</span>

## Verbalizing suffixes {#sec:vbz}
None of these are productive, although there are many lexemes derived with them.

### Intransitive

#### -ta / -na
[Morpheme tavbz](MorphsetTable?#cldf:tavbz) derives intransitive verbs.


<a id='tab:tavbz'></a><div class='caption table' id='tab:tavbz'>Lexemes derived with *-ta*</div>

| Base                                                                  | Derivation                                                                                    |
|:----------------------------------------------------------------------|:----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| [Lexeme suku-urine](LexemeTable?#cldf:suku-urine)                     | [Lexeme sujta-urinate](LexemeTable?#cldf:sujta-urinate)                                       |
| [Lexeme kaimo-game](LexemeTable?#cldf:kaimo-game)                     | [Lexeme kaimota-hunt](LexemeTable?#cldf:kaimota-hunt)                                         |
