## Person prefixes {#sec:verbperson}
Verbs are inflected for person with a set of prefixes, shown in <a href='#tab:verbprefixes' class='crossref' name='tab:verbprefixes' release=""False"" >ref</a>.
First and second person prefixes show ergative alignment, expressing <span class='smallcaps'>s</span> and <span class='smallcaps'>p</span>. <span title='count cases of expressing A'>❗️</span>
Intransitive verbs are not overtly inflected for third person, while transitive verbs show an optional [Morpheme t3](MorphsetTable?no_translation#cldf:t3) in <span class='smallcaps'>3</span>><span class='smallcaps'>3</span> scenarios.<span title='mentionworthy that this is not in alternation with preceding NPs'>❗️</span>


<a id='tab:verbprefixes'></a><div class='caption table' id='tab:verbprefixes'>Person marking prefixes on verbs</div>

|                                    | <span class='smallcaps'>intr</span>                   | <span class='smallcaps'>tr</span>                     |
|:-----------------------------------|:------------------------------------------------------|:------------------------------------------------------|
| <span class='smallcaps'>1</span>   | [Morpheme u1](MorphsetTable?no_translation#cldf:u1)   | [Morpheme u1](MorphsetTable?no_translation#cldf:u1)   |
| <span class='smallcaps'>2</span>   | [Morpheme me2](MorphsetTable?no_translation#cldf:me2) | [Morpheme me2](MorphsetTable?no_translation#cldf:me2) |
| <span class='smallcaps'>1+2</span> | _ej(n)-_                                              | _ej(n)-_                                              |
| <span class='smallcaps'>3</span>   | ∅                                                     | [Morpheme t3](MorphsetTable?no_translation#cldf:t3)   |

* one attested case of [Morpheme t3](MorphsetTable?translation=3>3#cldf:t3) on the lexical verb of a _-pëkë_ construction w/ 2nd person <span class='smallcaps'>a</span> on <span class='smallcaps'>aux</span> <span title='which one?'>❓</span>
    * Ø‑ ‘<span class='smallcaps'>3p</span>’ with transitive verbs with <span class='smallcaps'>1a</span> or <span class='smallcaps'>2a</span>
* one example of [Morpheme me2](MorphsetTable?#cldf:me2) ‘<span class='smallcaps'>2A</span>’ on imperative verb <span title='GrMePers.029'>❗️</span>
<span title='FM: u- is sometimes wï-, but usually not transcribed & distribution unclear'>❗️</span>


<span title='Check: appears that first and second person are reduced forms, with long vowel? wait for leila'>❓</span>

* \*_t‑V‑se_ is no more — the _t‑_ is gone, except in lexicalized items


